The paper focuses on regularization techniques for convolutional neural networks, which are commonly used in computer vision tasks such as image classification and object detection. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of machine learning techniques to adapt the regularization to the data, which suggests that it could also be relevant to categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
